Question 2:

joined13 = join(wine1, wine3, by = 'wine')
joined13$water.holding.capacity = recode(joined13$water.holding.capacity, '>200mm' = '≥200mm', "100-140mm" = '90-140mm', "90-120mm" = '90-140mm', "50-80mm" = '≤80mm', "<50mm" = '≤80mm')
#head(joined13)
wine1 = joined13[,c(1:16)]
#wine1
wine3 = joined13[,c(1,17,18,19,20)]
#wine3
wine1_prcomp = prcomp(wine1, scale. = FALSE)
ggbiplot(wine1_prcomp, scale = 0, var.axes = FALSE, group = wine3$water.holding.capacity)  +    scale_color_manual(values = c("≥200mm" = "darkblue", "90-140mm" = "firebrick", "≤80mm" = "green"))

wine1_lda = lda(x = wine1, grouping = wine3$water.holding.capacity)
ggbiplot(wine1_lda,groups = wine3$water.holding.capacity) + coord_equal(ratio = 10)
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.

According to the plot above, I think it suggested that the relationship between the water holding capacities of the soil and the fermentative volatile compounds for each wine is similar except FAEE.
